## Example 4 — Determine Which Similarity Criterion Applies

$\triangle JKL$ has $\angle J = 72°$, $\angle K = 48°$, and $JK = 10$. $\triangle MNP$ has $\angle M = 72°$, $\angle N = 60°$, and $MN = 15$. Are the triangles similar?

### Step 1: Find the Third Angle of Each Triangle

$$\triangle JKL: \angle L = 180° - 72° - 48° = 60°$$

$$\triangle MNP: \angle P = 180° - 72° - 60° = 48°$$

### Step 2: Match Corresponding Angles

$$\angle J = 72° = \angle M$$

$$\angle K = 48° = \angle P$$

$$\angle L = 60° = \angle N$$

Two pairs of congruent angles exist ($\angle J \cong \angle M$ and $\angle K \cong \angle P$).

### Step 3: Apply AA Similarity

$$\triangle JKL \sim \triangle MNP \text{ by AA Similarity}$$

The correspondence is $J \leftrightarrow M$, $K \leftrightarrow P$, $L \leftrightarrow N$.

✅ Answer: The triangles are similar by **AA Similarity**.

